654
00:49:36,202 --> 00:49:39,103
I been thinkin' about
goin' to a psychiatrist.

655
00:49:39,105 --> 00:49:41,739
Now, where am I gonna get
that kind of money?

656
00:49:41,741 --> 00:49:43,006
Shit!

657
00:49:44,942 --> 00:49:47,210
Told her she should have
just let me take her.

658
00:49:47,212 --> 00:49:50,080
She wrote me some
dumb-ass letter.

659
00:49:50,082 --> 00:49:51,948
It broke her heart, Greta,

660
00:49:51,950 --> 00:49:54,283
honest to god, but you gotta
try and be proud of her.

661
00:49:54,285 --> 00:49:57,019
She thinks she's doing
something right in her life.

662
00:50:01,858 --> 00:50:05,860
You know how old I was
when I had my first beer?

663
00:50:05,862 --> 00:50:07,629
12.

664
00:50:08,764 --> 00:50:10,265
You know where I was?

665
00:50:10,267 --> 00:50:12,100
Your basement.

666
00:50:12,102 --> 00:50:13,635
Hey, I know your daddy.

667
00:50:13,637 --> 00:50:15,837
There wasn't any shortage
at your place.

668
00:50:48,267 --> 00:50:50,801
No pigtoes.

669
00:50:50,803 --> 00:50:52,670
No pigtoes here, either.

670
00:50:54,139 --> 00:50:57,241
Gotta find a spot
with deeper water.

671
00:50:57,243 --> 00:50:58,742
Did you read that somewhere?

672
00:50:58,744 --> 00:51:00,044
No.

673
00:51:01,012 --> 00:51:03,346
But pigtoes need fish
to reproduce.

674
00:51:03,348 --> 00:51:06,215
It was too shallow over
there for fish to swim.

675
00:51:08,619 --> 00:51:09,986
You gotta get in.

676
00:51:12,089 --> 00:51:13,956
It's just water.

677
00:51:26,935 --> 00:51:29,103
- I found one.
