687
00:51:58,132 --> 00:52:00,965
That's it.

688
00:52:00,967 --> 00:52:02,300
I think I got it.

689
00:52:02,302 --> 00:52:04,869
There's no way you're
catching up with me.

690
00:52:20,084 --> 00:52:22,285
Do you want to go in?

691
00:52:23,420 --> 00:52:25,087
No.

692
00:52:25,089 --> 00:52:28,024
Should we wait here
till your mom gets back?

693
00:52:28,026 --> 00:52:31,093
My mom ran away.

694
00:52:31,095 --> 00:52:32,662
What do you mean?

695
00:52:32,664 --> 00:52:35,830
I mean she packed up her
stuff and drove away.

696
00:52:35,832 --> 00:52:37,932
I thought you said your mo...
I lied.

697
00:52:38,964 --> 00:52:41,586
I didn't want you to make a big
deal about the whole thing.

698
00:52:48,810 --> 00:52:50,444
We moved here when I was 5.

699
00:52:50,446 --> 00:52:53,747
This was our first
house together.

700
00:52:53,749 --> 00:52:56,916
Before that, we lived
at my grandma's.

701
00:52:56,918 --> 00:52:58,418
Is that where you live now?

702
00:53:01,855 --> 00:53:04,090
What about your dad?

703
00:53:05,125 --> 00:53:08,760
He was a business
student at Rend Lake.

704
00:53:08,762 --> 00:53:12,731
He was killed in a motorcycle
crash when I was 2.

705
00:53:12,733 --> 00:53:15,100
I never met him.

706
00:53:18,137 --> 00:53:20,705
Will you take my picture?

707
00:54:58,363 --> 00:55:00,396
Jesus!

708
00:55:00,398 --> 00:55:01,531
Ree!

709
00:55:03,232 --> 00:55:05,200
You scared me.

710
00:55:06,402 --> 00:55:09,838
Lauduree.

711
00:55:09,840 --> 00:55:11,206
Lauduree.

712
00:55:12,842 --> 00:55:14,142
Honey.

713
00:55:16,479 --> 00:55:18,145
Come on, you gotta wake up.

714
00:55:18,147 --> 00:55:20,314
