719
00:55:34,529 --> 00:55:36,863
How come?

720
00:55:36,865 --> 00:55:38,597
Well, 'cause I like it.

721
00:55:38,599 --> 00:55:40,966
What are you doing up
past your bedtime?

722
00:55:40,968 --> 00:55:42,334
You said I could.

723
00:55:44,070 --> 00:55:46,171
I don't recall that.

724
00:55:46,173 --> 00:55:48,307
You said it was a new
first date rule.

725
00:55:48,309 --> 00:55:51,242
Lauduree, I don't know
what you're talking about.

726
00:55:51,244 --> 00:55:52,543
<i>Mom.</i>

727
00:55:57,282 --> 00:55:59,617
Remember that guy you
dated when I was 9?

728
00:55:59,619 --> 00:56:02,886
He was bald and had a ponytail?

729
00:56:02,888 --> 00:56:04,888
Good french inhale.

730
00:56:04,890 --> 00:56:07,424
Jim Polecock.

731
00:56:07,426 --> 00:56:09,526
Yeah, that's right.

732
00:56:09,528 --> 00:56:13,128
He called Crystal Betty Grable,

733
00:56:13,486 --> 00:56:15,516
- and you Gene Tierney.
- I didn't know that.

734
00:56:15,867 --> 00:56:17,867
Yeah, 'cause you were
both beautiful.

735
00:56:17,869 --> 00:56:21,637
But Crystal was an airhead,
and you were tragic.

736
00:56:21,639 --> 00:56:23,938
God, if he only knew.

737
00:56:23,940 --> 00:56:27,108
And he called Gigi Bette.
Bette for...

738
00:56:27,110 --> 00:56:29,911
- Bette Davis?
- Yeah.

739
00:56:29,913 --> 00:56:31,012
Huh.

740
00:56:33,582 --> 00:56:36,917
Hey, do you remember
the nursing home?

741
00:56:36,919 --> 00:56:38,018
Yeah.

742
00:56:38,020 --> 00:56:39,519
They kicked you out, though,

743
00:56:39,521 --> 00:56:41,588
'cause you made all the old
ladies look like movie stars.

744
00:56:41,590 --> 00:56:44,458
God, they loved her there.

745
00:56:44,460 --> 00:56:46,559
That was a great job,

746
00:56:46,561 --> 00:56:48,227
and you know,
I got her that job.

747
00:56:48,229 --> 00:56:51,163
She was at her best then.

748
00:56:51,165 --> 00:56:54,033
Think you'll ever get married?

749
00:56:56,470 --> 00:56:57,602
No.

750
00:56:58,938 --> 00:57:00,572
Why?

751
00:57:00,574 --> 00:57:03,408
'Cause I stay up late,
and they get up early.

752
00:57:03,410 --> 00:57:05,243
Well, that's sorta dumb.

753
00:57:05,245 --> 00:57:08,346
Yeah, well...

754
00:57:08,348 --> 00:57:10,147
I don't trust men.

755
00:57:10,149 --> 00:57:11,415
Why not?

756
00:57:15,353 --> 00:57:17,421
I met a bad one once.

757
00:57:19,157 --> 00:57:21,291
He kind of ruined the rest.

758
00:57:26,997 --> 00:57:29,966
All right, come on.

759
00:57:29,968 --> 00:57:32,167
Gotta get you up to bed.

760
00:57:32,169 --> 00:57:33,936
It's okay.

761
00:57:34,387 --> 00:57:36,200
It's grandma. It's Gigi.

762
00:57:37,057 --> 00:57:38,882
- Gigi?
- Yeah.

